leadership-approach|process_results_vision_people|concentrated|process|results|vision|people|You may be recognised for Process first|You may recognise yourself in the way you notice messy handovers, unclear steps, or avoidable rework before anything else. Others may experience more order, steadier standards, and a clearer path for others to follow, especially when the work needs someone to make the work easier to organise and repeat.|This can make leadership feel easier when Process gives others something clear to orient around. It can become harder when the structure keeps improving after the situation needs movement, direction, or a human conversation, so Results, Vision, or People may need to be invited earlier.|active|leadership-approach::process_results_vision_people::concentrated
