leadership-approach|vision_results_people_process|balanced|vision|results|people|process|You may move between Vision, Results, People, and Process|You may recognise yourself in moving between several leadership routes rather than relying on only one. Vision may appear first, but Results, People, and Process can all become the right route when the situation changes.|This can make leadership feel easier because you have several usable routes into the work. It can become harder if you change route before others know which one matters now, so naming the current need becomes important.|active|leadership-approach::vision_results_people_process::balanced
leadership-approach|vision_process_results_people|concentrated|vision|process|results|people|You may be recognised for Vision first|You may recognise yourself in the way you notice short-term thinking, flat plans, or decisions without a clear reason before anything else. Others may experience a stronger frame, more possibility, and a clearer reason for change, especially when the work needs someone to connect the work to a wider direction.|This can make leadership feel easier when Vision gives others something clear to orient around. It can become harder when the future frame stays too high-level for decisions, structure, or people to act on, so Process, Results, or People may need to be invited earlier.|active|leadership-approach::vision_process_results_people::concentrated
leadership-approach|vision_process_results_people|paired|vision|process|results|people|Vision and Process may work as a close pair|You may recognise yourself in the way Vision and Process come together under pressure. Others may experience a stronger frame, more possibility, and a clearer reason for change, with Process helping the approach become more usable.|This can make leadership feel easier when the pair handles both the main pressure and the practical follow-through. It can become harder if the pair runs ahead of Results or People, which may be the range that keeps the work rounded.|active|leadership-approach::vision_process_results_people::paired
