leadership-approach|vision_people_process_results|graduated|vision|people|process|results|Your leadership may move from Vision towards Results|You may recognise yourself in a stepped leadership rhythm: Vision starts the work, People gives it more range, Process adds support, and Results may need to be brought in deliberately.|This can make leadership feel easier because the order gives you a natural sequence to follow. It can become harder if the later signals are left until the work has already narrowed, especially Results.|active|leadership-approach::vision_people_process_results::graduated
leadership-approach|vision_people_process_results|balanced|vision|people|process|results|You may move between Vision, People, Process, and Results|You may recognise yourself in moving between several leadership routes rather than relying on only one. Vision may appear first, but People, Process, and Results can all become the right route when the situation changes.|This can make leadership feel easier because you have several usable routes into the work. It can become harder if you change route before others know which one matters now, so naming the current need becomes important.|active|leadership-approach::vision_people_process_results::balanced
leadership-approach|people_results_process_vision|concentrated|people|results|process|vision|You may be recognised for People first|You may recognise yourself in the way you notice low confidence, unclear buy-in, or people being left behind by the pace of work before anything else. Others may experience more trust, better communication, and stronger shared understanding, especially when the work needs someone to keep trust and commitment visible in the work.|This can make leadership feel easier when People gives others something clear to orient around. It can become harder when care for people delays a decision, structure, or future direction the work now needs, so Results, Process, or Vision may need to be invited earlier.|active|leadership-approach::people_results_process_vision::concentrated
